    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for an initial 10-12 min or until almost fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> to a plate with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced flour</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and coat in the spiced flour</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated fish </strong>and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden, crispy and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>curried fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 10-12 min, add the<strong> trimmed green beans </strong>to the pot with the potatoes and cook for a final 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a generous knob of<strong> butter</strong> to the pot with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground cumin</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook over a medium heat for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>spinach </strong>and cook for a final 1-2 min or until wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>gunpowder potatoes & beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/curried-basa-with-gunpowder-potatoes-and-green-beans-and-mint-chutney/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy curried fish </strong>with the <strong>gunpowder potatoes</strong> <strong>& green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>mint & coriander chutney</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
